Aidan Baker Collaborations.title: Laika World
Aidan Baker Collaborations.artist: Aidan Baker | Jack Chuter | Ryan Durfee
Aidan Baker Collaborations.label: Broken Spine Productions
Aidan Baker Collaborations.about:
LAIKA WORLD is a collaborative album by Aidan Baker, Jack Chuter, and Ryan Durfee, created in tribute to Laika, the Soviet space dog who became the first animal to orbit Earth aboard Sputnik 2 on November 3, 1957.
The album is a sonic blend of diverse influences, including Dean Hurley, SpaceGhostPurrp, Starflyer 59, Emeralds, Flying Saucer Attack, painter Morris Graves, and the films of Renee Harmon and Takeshi Kitano. Birdsong detonates from within sweeps of reverbed guitar, synthesiser and hypnagogic vocal spill, while frenetic drums keep an intermittent sense of time.
Ideal for those who enjoy late-night conversations and the vivid dreams that follow.
Limited cassette available from Cruel Nature Recordings:
cruelnaturerecordings.bandcamp.com/album/laika-world
Aidan Baker Collaborations.credits:
released October 25, 2024
Aidan Baker - drums, percussion
Jack Chuter - guitar, voice, synth, samples
Ryan Durfee - field recordings, Korg WaveState, Koala

Aidan Baker Collaborations.title: Thoughts of Trio
Aidan Baker Collaborations.artist: Aidan Baker | Han-earl Park | Katharina Schmidt
Aidan Baker Collaborations.label: Broken Spine Productions
Aidan Baker Collaborations.about:
Thoughts of Trio documents a live-in-studio performance by Canadian guitarist Aidan Baker, Korean-American guitarist Han-earl Park, & German drummer/percussionist Katharina Schmidt. The group brings together their respective, disparate musical backgrounds to explore the intersections of ambient music, improvisational (free) jazz, and musique-concrète.
Recorded at Morphine Raum in Berlin, Germany on February 21, 2024 by Rabih Beaini.
Released on CD by Attenuation Circuit and cassette by Cruel Nature Recordings:
emerge.bandcamp.com/album/thoughts-of-trio
cruelnaturerecordings.bandcamp.com/album/thoughts-of-trio

Aidan Baker Collaborations.about:
Fourth in a series of five Trio Not Trio CD releases from Gizeh Records, each album with a different trio line-up, recorded as a duo in person in Berlin and completed long-distance by a third, international musician.
This fourth album features British drummer Tobias Humble (also of Lawns,Tricky, Mick Harvey, etc.) and Japanese vocalist/electronic musician Ayami Suzuki (aka Sand Fountain):

www.ayamisuzuki.jp

Aidan Baker Collaborations.title: Trzecia (Drugi)
Aidan Baker Collaborations.artist: Aidan Baker, Tim Wyskida, Daron Beck
Aidan Baker Collaborations.label: Broken Spine Productions
Aidan Baker Collaborations.about:
In 2023, Aidan Baker (Nadja, Tavare), Daron Beck (Pinkish Black), and Tim Wyskida (Khanate, Blind Idiot God, Insect Ark) came together through Baker’s Trio Not Trio series for Gizeh Records—an experiment in presence and distance. Two musicians met in Berlin for a live, improvised session; a third joined from another part of the world, layering sound and response from afar. What emerged blurred the line between physical space and shared intention, finding new textures in the space between.
Their contribution, "Trzecia," became one of the most resonant works in the series—a convergence of weight, tone, and atmosphere that felt both immediate and remote, human and spectral. The trio soon began work on a second recording using the same process, extending the conversation they had begun. Before the final mixes could be completed, Daron Beck sadly passed away.
"Trzecia (Drugi)" gathers fragments from those later sessions that trace the contours of what might have been, and what still remains. It stands as both continuation and memorial, a quiet offering to Beck’s enduring presence within the sound.
Released as a limited edition cassette from Cruel Nature Recordings:
cruelnaturerecordings.bandcamp.com/album/trzecia-drugi
And an even more limited edition lathe-cut 7" from Skew Note:
skewnote.bandcamp.com/album/trzecia-drugi
Recorded in Berlin and Austin in 2024
Tim Wyskida plays Canopus Drums
Artwork 'Elysian Doorway' by Derek R. Setzer -  dereksetzer.com
